:: How to split a string, but also keep the delimiters?
   
    You can use Lookahead and Lookbehind. Like this:
    System.out.println(Arrays.toString("a;b;c;d".split("(?<=;)")));
       output:   [a;, b;, c;, d]
    System.out.println(Arrays.toString("a;b;c;d".split("(?=;)")));
       output:   [a, ;b, ;c, ;d]
    System.out.println(Arrays.toString("a;b;c;d".split("((?<=;)|(?=;))")));
       output:   [a, ;, b, ;, c, ;, d] 
